From 1ac30689fc59d4ea6ee4ba9875a36285316a4dc3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 06:21:40 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 40/65] media: rockchip: rga: use snapshotted task count in
 debug dump

Plain-language impact:
The request-manager dump now walks only the copied task entries.

Kernel details:
rga_request_manager_show() snapshots task_count under request->lock; iterate over that snapshot instead of live request->task_count.

Source: split from patches/cleanup-draft after docs/11-bsp-audit.md verification.
Signed-off-by: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_debugger.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_debugger.c b/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_debugger.c
index ddce4b5385a5..ae3c1c0efed7 100644
--- a/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_debugger.c
+++ b/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_debugger.c
@@ -375,7 +375,7 @@ static int rga_request_manager_show(struct seq_file *m, void *data)
 
 		seq_puts(m, "\t cmd dump:\n\n");
 
-		for (i = 0; i < request->task_count; i++)
+		for (i = 0; i < task_count; i++)
 			rga_request_task_debug_info(m, &(task_list[i]));
 	}
 
